# Copy to .env and fill in. Loaded automatically at startup (see cadio/config.py).
# Without GOOGLE_* set, the app runs in local-dev mode: a single implicit user,
# no sign-in screen (a "local dev" badge shows instead of sign-out).

# --- Google OAuth (enables real sign-in/out) ---
# Create these in Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials →
# OAuth 2.0 Client ID (type: Web application). See the setup steps below.
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Signing key for the session cookie. REQUIRED once OAuth is on, or sessions
# reset on every restart. Generate one:  python -c "import secrets;print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
CADIO_SESSION_SECRET=

# --- Optional beta allowlist (comma-separated emails, and/or a domain) ---
# If unset, anyone Google authenticates is allowed — gate via the Google Console
# "Testing" consent screen's test-user list instead.
# CADIO_ALLOWED_EMAILS=you@example.com,teammate@example.com
# CADIO_ALLOWED_DOMAIN=example.com

# --- Local dev over Vite (http://localhost:5173) ---
# The OAuth round-trip must land on the FRONTEND origin (Vite proxies /api to the
# backend), and the session cookie can't be Secure over plain http. Set BOTH for
# local dev, and register the redirect URI below in Google Console.
# CADIO_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:5173/api/auth/callback
# CADIO_COOKIE_SECURE=false
# (In production behind one https origin, omit both — the defaults are correct.)

# --- Optional tuning ---
# CADIO_DAILY_RUN_QUOTA=300
# CADIO_LOG_LEVEL=INFO          # DEBUG traces every websocket message

# --- Split deployment: separate frontend + backend containers (optional) ---
# Leave unset for single-origin (dev Vite proxy, or the old combined image).
# Set when the frontend runs as its OWN container on a different origin:
#   CADIO_FRONTEND_URL  the frontend's browser origin(s), comma-separated. Enables
#                       CORS (with credentials) and is where OAuth returns users.
#   CADIO_PUBLIC_URL    this backend's own public base URL, so artifact/preview
#                       links come back absolute and load from the API origin.
# CADIO_FRONTEND_URL=https://app.example.com
# CADIO_PUBLIC_URL=https://api.example.com
# The FRONTEND container takes its own env var (not read here) to find the API:
#   BACKEND_URL=https://api.example.com
# With split origins, sign-in needs Secure cookies over HTTPS (SameSite=None is
# set automatically) and the OAuth redirect URI must point at the BACKEND origin:
#   CADIO_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=https://api.example.com/api/auth/callback

# --- Database backend (optional) ---
# Unset  -> SQLite at ~/.cadio/cadio.db (single box, zero setup).
# Set    -> the whole metadata store moves to Postgres/Supabase; nothing else
#           changes. Use Supabase's POOLED connection string (port 6543,
#           transaction mode) for the app:
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.<ref>:<password>@aws-0-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres

# --- Object storage: Cloudflare R2 (optional) ---
# Unset R2_* -> run artifacts live only on local disk (fine on one persistent
#   volume). Set all four creds -> disk becomes a write-through cache in front of
#   R2, which holds the durable copy. R2 has zero egress fees but NO hard spend
#   cap, so the caps below are ENFORCED in-app (cadio/storage.py) to stay inside
#   the free tier: storage via LRU eviction, Class A/B ops via a monthly counter.
# NOTE: keep each value on its own line with NO trailing "# comment" — Docker's
# --env-file treats everything after '=' as the value, comment included.
# R2_ACCOUNT_ID=
# R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# R2_BUCKET=cadio
# R2_ENDPOINT is optional — derived from R2_ACCOUNT_ID if left unset:
# R2_ENDPOINT=
# Free-tier caps (defaults sit just under R2's 10GB / 1M / 10M free limits):
# 9.5 GB (limit 10 GB):
# R2_MAX_STORAGE_BYTES=9500000000
# writes/month (limit 1M):
# R2_MAX_CLASS_A_OPS=950000
# reads/month (limit 10M):
# R2_MAX_CLASS_B_OPS=9500000

# --- LLM provider keys (optional; users can also enter their own in the UI) ---
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Google Cloud Console setup (one time):
#  1. Create/select a project.
#  2. OAuth consent screen: External, scopes openid/email/profile (non-sensitive,
#     no verification needed). Keep publishing status "Testing" and add your
#     Google account under Test users (this doubles as the beta allowlist).
#  3. Credentials → Create OAuth client ID → Web application.
#  4. Authorized redirect URIs (add both — `cadio serve` defaults to 127.0.0.1,
#     but some setups/browsers land on localhost instead; Google requires an
#     exact string match so either one alone will 400 for the other):
#       http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/auth/callback        (local)
#       http://localhost:8000/api/auth/callback        (local)
#       https://YOUR_DOMAIN/api/auth/callback          (prod)
#  5. Copy the Client ID/secret above, set CADIO_SESSION_SECRET, restart the app.
#  6. First sign-in with your Google account inherits all existing projects.
